**Scheduling rules:**
- A `-` in any column means **skip that transition** for that day. Do not invent a timestamp for it. Mild days may have no peak_stress. Stable-sky days may have no cloud_shift.
- **Schedule transitions in chronological order**, not column order. On some days, `decline` occurs before `peak_stress` (solar peaks early, VPD peaks later due to thermal lag). Sort your transitions by timestamp.
- If two milestones share the **same timestamp**, merge them into one transition. Use the more aggressive posture and mention both semantics in the `reason` field.
- Emit fewer transitions on easy days. Not every day needs 6 transitions.

